node.text:
Yoga and Meditation with Guru Turtle 🧘🏼‍♂️ Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on tripfever.net (link in my bio: @tripfever)

This unique type of meditation is all about relaxation and being one with the ocean 🌿😄

The Great Barrier Reef in the Australian estate of Queensland is home to six out of seven of the world's sea turtle species. Not only this coast is radiant with sunshine, but its picturesque landscapes are also overflowing with an impressive population of native animals.

From witnessing baby turtles make their way to the sea to see adult turtles enjoying @nature, that's a magical sight to behold.

Tag your @nature lovers friends! 🐢

📽 @jacintashackleton
📍 Queensland, Australia
🎶 Arnaud Gauthier - Yoga

node.text:
Have you ever seen this colorful community? 😍 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on tripfever.net (link in my bio: @tripfever)

Its located in Rainbow island, Iran. This colorful residence of dirt domes was built by Nader Khalili and its a beach front residence community.

Hormuz Island sits south of Iran in the Persian Gulf and is often called “rainbow island” in reference to the multicolored sand that makes it a popular tourist spot. In an effort to reflect the colorful landscape and topography, ZAV Architects has designed a small settlement comprising multicolor domes that overlap in interesting combinations to create homes and cultural programs such as laundry services, praying areas, and a café.

This multipurpose settlement, referred to as Presence in Hormuz, serves as more than just a bright and welcoming accommodation, though—it is the embodiment of a paradigm shift for the community. “The local inhabitants of the beautiful, touristic and politically strategic island,” the architects explain, “struggle economically, getting involved in illegal trafficking activities using their boats.” This urban development project aims to reinvigorate the local economy by utilizing members of the community—craftsmen and unskilled workers alike.

1, 4. @iranianmarcopolo
2. @raheleh.mamaghani
3, 5, 6, 7, 8 & 9. @themagger
📍Hormoz Island, Iran
